#~ "<filename> ~/.kde/share/apps/krusader/krusaderui.rc</filename> and re-run "
#~ "&krusader;. If you have compiled &krusader; from sources this is often "
#~ "caused if the <envar>KDEDIR</envar> - <envar>QTDIR</envar> environment "
#~ "variables are not correctly set. The result is that the "
#~ "<filename>krusaderui.rc</filename> file is installed in the wrong "
#~ "directory. Please read the following question, as well."
